### Bioinformatic pipeline followed to do haplotype calling of Oophaga granulifera RNA reads using
the genome of Oophaga sylvatica and a species-specific superTranscriptome as references ###

Main steps included:
1- RNA reads quality trimming
2- SuperTranscriptome assembly
3- Generation of genome or SuperTranscriptome index
4- Mapping reads against reference using STAR
5- Mark duplicates
6- Merge tissues per individuals
7- Fix groups ID
8- SplitNCigar 
9- GATK Haplotype Calling
10- GATK Merge individuals
11- VCF postprocessing


For each step I provide the used script. Note that all bioinformatic analyses were conducted in a remote server of HPC from the Emmy/Grete at NHR–Nord@Göttingen.
Accounts, and resource allocation to different nodes and partitions might vary, and are not provided here

The files used for each analysis are available either in this github directory or in Zenodo: https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17805830
See related publication for more details on data availability
